Reports said the international star arrived in the resort town as part of his tour of African countries.He reportedly arrived in Livingstone that day and was thought to be booked in one of the hotels at the Zambian border town.The state media in Zimbabwe said Smith "visited the Victoria Falls and did Bunjee jumping" on Thursday afternoon.In Zimbabwe, Smith is remembered for his role in the popular TV series, Fresh Prince of Bel-Air, which was popular in the country in the mid 1990's.He is also known for his role in The Pursuit of Happiness, Man in Black, Bad Boys and Independence Day, among others.